      <p>To convert these weights into transition probabilities {α<sub>0</sub>, …, α<sub><italic toggle="yes">K</italic> + 1</sub>}, we need to account for the fact that the weights are contributing to a Boltzmann distribution that is being normalized by a partition function. Because of the partition function, preserving an identical Boltzmann distribution while rescaling the weights requires that the weight for each DBF be rescaled by an amount that accounts for its length. Specifically, for any choice of positive constant <italic toggle="yes">c</italic>, the weight of DBF <italic toggle="yes">k</italic> must be rescaled by <inline-formula><tex-math id="M33">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
